For question answering over knowledge bases, it is important to know whether a KB can be relied upon in terms of complete answer sets [darari2013completeness, hopkinson2018demand,DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2001-04425]. Current coverage estimation techniques for KBs do this analysis only post-hoc after the KB is fully constructed [galarraga2017predicting, luggen2019non], losing access to valuable information from extraction time.